.TH "ccwchain_calc_length" 9 "ccwchain_calc_length" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ccwchain_calc_length \- calculate the length of the ccw chain.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ccwchain_calc_length
.BI "(u64 iova "  ","
.BI "struct channel_program *cp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "iova" 12
guest physical address of the target ccw chain
.IP "cp" 12
channel_program on which to perform the operation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the chain length not considering any TICs.
You need to do a new round for each TIC target.

The program is also validated for absence of not yet supported
indirect data addressing scenarios.
.SH "RETURN"
the length of the ccw chain or -errno.
